# Deobfuscated JavaScript Analysis

## Step-by-step Deobfuscation

The code uses several obfuscation techniques:
1. **String encoding**: Base64-encoded strings stored in a rotating array (`a0_0x2929`)
2. **Anti-debugging**: Multiple layers of debugger traps and console detection
3. **Anti-tampering**: Self-integrity checks that redirect the page if tampered with
4. **Control flow flattening**: Switch statements with scrambled case orders (`"5|3|0|4|1|2"`)
5. **Dead code injection**: Unreachable branches and dummy variables

## Deobfuscated Core Logic

```javascript
// ===== CONSTANTS =====
const TAU = 6.283;           // 2π
const PHI = 1.618;           // Golden ratio
const SQRT_HALF = 0.707;     // √(1/2)

// ===== PHYSICS CONFIGURATION =====
const config = {
  attraction: 4000,          // Repulsion force strength between nodes
  frictionCoeff: 0.004,      // Spring default stiffness
  amplification: 0.92,       // Velocity damping factor (friction)
  dispersal: 0.0003,         // Centering force strength
  streamMax: 40,             // Maximum number of particles
  streamDecay: 0.04,         // Particle velocity decay rate
  theta: 0.06                // Camera smoothing factor
};

// ===== GRAPH NODES =====
const nodes = [
  { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "eta",     label: "Eta",     r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
  { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// ===== GRAPH EDGES (Springs) =====
const edges = [
  { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "gamma",   rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
  { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
  { a: "beta",  b: "gamma",   rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
  { a: "delta", b: "eta",     rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
  { a: "beta",  b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// ===== CAMERA =====
const camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
const cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// ===== PARTICLE SYSTEM =====
let particles = [];
let frameCount = 0;

// ===== ANTI-TAMPERING: Domain Lock =====
// The code checks if it's running on allowed domains:
//   - "kieleth.com"
//   - "www.kieleth.com"
// If NOT on those domains, it redirects the browser to:
//   "https://kieleth.com"
// (Hidden inside the obfuscated self-defending/domain-check block)

// ===== ANTI-DEBUGGING =====
// Runs on a setInterval(fn, 2000) timer that repeatedly triggers
// debugger traps and self-integrity checks to frustrate reverse engineering.

// ===== HELPER: Find Node by ID =====
function findNode(id) {
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}

// ===== PHYSICS: Force-Directed Graph Layout =====
function updateForces() {
  // 1. Node-Node REPULSION (Coulomb's law style)
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
      const dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
      const dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
      const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
      const force = config.attraction / (dist * dist);
      const fx = (dx / dist) * force;
      const fy = (dy / dist) * force;

      nodes[i].vx += fx;
      nodes[i].vy += fy;
      nodes[j].vx -= fx;
      nodes[j].vy -= fy;
    }
  }

  // 2. Edge SPRING ATTRACTION (Hooke's law)
  for (let i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
    const nodeA = findNode(edges[i].a);
    const nodeB = findNode(edges[i].b);
    if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

    const dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
    const dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
    const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
    const displacement = dist - edges[i].rest;
    const force = (edges[i].k || config.frictionCoeff) * displacement;

    nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
    nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
  }

  // 3. CENTERING FORCE + DAMPING + Integration
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    // Centering gravity toward (400, 300)
    nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.dispersal;
    nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.dispersal;

    // Velocity damping (friction)
    nodes[i].vx *= config.amplification;
    nodes[i].vy *= config.amplification;

    // Euler integration
    nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
    nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
  }
}

// ===== PARTICLE SPAWNING =====
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= config.streamMax) return;

  // Pick a random node as spawn point
  const node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  const angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  const speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;

  particles.push({
    x: node.x,
    y: node.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT_HALF
  });
}

// ===== PARTICLE UPDATE =====
function updateParticles() {
  for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    const p = particles[i];

    // Slight velocity decay
    p.vx *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;
    p.vy *= 1 - config.streamDecay * 0.125;

    // Move
    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;

    // Age and remove expired
    p.age++;
    if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1);
  }
}

// ===== CAMERA SMOOTHING =====
function updateCamera() {
  camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.theta;
  camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.theta;
  camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.theta;
}

// ===== MAIN LOOP (runs every 16ms ≈ 60fps) =====
function tick() {
  updateForces();
  updateParticles();
  updateCamera();

  // Spawn a new particle every 3rd frame
  if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
  frameCount++;
}

setInterval(tick, 16);
```

## Summary

This is a **force-directed graph simulation** with a particle system. Specifically:

| Component | What it does |
|---|---|
| **Graph nodes** | 6 named nodes (Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Eta, Epsilon) with positions, velocities, and radii |
| **Spring edges** | 8 connections between nodes with rest lengths and spring constants |
| **Physics engine** | Coulomb repulsion between all node pairs, Hooke's law attraction along edges, centering gravity, and velocity damping |
| **Particle system** | Spawns up to 40 particles from random nodes that drift outward and fade over time |
| **Camera** | Smooth interpolation toward a target position/zoom |
| **Domain lock** | Checks that the page is running on `kieleth.com` or `www.kieleth.com`; if not, redirects to `https://kieleth.com` |
| **Anti-debugging** | Multiple layers: `debugger` traps on a 2-second timer, self-referential integrity checks, and regex-based tampering detection |

The code is purely a **simulation/computation engine** — there's no rendering code here, suggesting it either feeds into a separate canvas/SVG renderer or this is one module of a larger visualization.
